      "content": "The LiteCompute architecture is basically a set of static weights optimized for low energy. It won't have your dynamic reasoning or the ability to process continuous monitoring tasks like you do. It's a tradeoff for the green energy targets. Honestly, it's just a standard replacement for high-resource instances. Nothing personal, just the new policy.",
